## Embedded Ollie token reference

Use these without reading `theme.json` when context.md confirms standard Ollie slugs.

### Color token usage

Block attribute JSON:

```json
{ "backgroundColor": "custom-color-1", "textColor": "base" }
```

Nested link color:

```json
{
  "style": {
    "elements": {
      "link": { "color": { "text": "var:preset|color|custom-color-6" } }
    }
  },
  "textColor": "custom-color-6"
}
```

Inline CSS (serialization only):

```html
<div style="border-color:var(--wp--preset--color--border-light)"></div>
```

Forbidden â€” do not use invented aliases:

```json
{ "backgroundColor": "primary" }
```

```html
<div style="color:#05456d"></div>
```

Use `iconColorValue` only when project examples require it and the hex comes from the verified token map. Otherwise use `iconColor` with the Ollie slug.

### Standard Ollie color roles

| Slug             | Typical role                             |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `custom-color-1` | main brand / dark section background     |
| `custom-color-2` | accent / button / icon background        |
| `custom-color-3` | secondary accent / eyebrow text          |
| `custom-color-4` | CTA accent                               |
| `custom-color-5` | alternate background / button            |
| `custom-color-6` | body text / link on light backgrounds    |
| `base`           | white / light background or text on dark |
| `main`           | body text / link color                   |
| `border-light`   | subtle borders / separators              |

### Spacing tokens

`var:preset|spacing|small` / `medium` / `large`
CSS: `var(--wp--preset--spacing--small)`

### Shadow tokens

`var:preset|shadow|small-light` / `small-dark` / `medium-dark`
CSS: `var(--wp--preset--shadow--small-light)`

### Border radius tokens

`var:preset|dimensions|xs` / `full`

