## Embedded block pattern examples

Use these directly. Do not re-read pattern files to calibrate style.

### PHP pattern skeleton

```php
<?php
return array(
	'title'         => __( 'Pattern Title', 'dhali' ),
	'categories'    => array( 'dhali-web-development', 'card' ),
	'description'   => _x( 'One sentence describing the pattern.', 'Block pattern description', 'dhali' ),
	'keywords'      => array( 'keyword', 'section' ),
	'viewportWidth' => 1000,
	'blockTypes'    => array( 'core/group' ),
	'content'       => '
        <!-- wp:group {"metadata":{"name":"Section"},"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"constrained"}} -->
        <div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:heading {"textColor":"custom-color-1"} -->
        <h2 class="wp-block-heading has-custom-color-1-color has-text-color">Section heading</h2>
        <!-- /wp:heading --></div>
        <!-- /wp:group -->
    ',
);
```

### Section heading group with animation

```html
<!-- wp:group {"metadata":{"name":"Section Heading"},"style":{"spacing":{"blockGap":"0"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","justifyContent":"center"},"animationType":"fadeInDown","animateOnScroll":true} -->
<div class="wp-block-group">
  <!-- wp:heading {"level":3,"textColor":"custom-color-3"} -->
  <h3 class="wp-block-heading has-custom-color-3-color has-text-color">
    Eyebrow
  </h3>
  <!-- /wp:heading -->

  <!-- wp:heading {"textColor":"custom-color-1"} -->
  <h2 class="wp-block-heading has-custom-color-1-color has-text-color">
    Main heading
  </h2>
  <!-- /wp:heading -->
</div>
<!-- /wp:group -->
```

### Card with shadow and hover animation

```html
<!-- wp:group {"metadata":{"name":"Card"},"style":{"spacing":{"blockGap":"var:preset|spacing|small","padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|medium","right":"var:preset|spacing|medium","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|medium","left":"var:preset|spacing|medium"}},"shadow":"var:preset|shadow|small-light"},"backgroundColor":"base","layout":{"type":"constrained"},"animationType":"scaleOnHover"} -->
<div
  class="wp-block-group has-base-background-color has-background"
  style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--medium);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--medium);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--medium);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--medium);box-shadow:var(--wp--preset--shadow--small-light)"
>
  <!-- child blocks -->
</div>
<!-- /wp:group -->
```

### Button group (primary + ghost)

```html
<!-- wp:buttons {"animationType":"scaleOnHover"} -->
<div class="wp-block-buttons">
  <!-- wp:button {"backgroundColor":"custom-color-2","textColor":"base","style":{"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|base"}}}}} -->
  <div class="wp-block-button">
    <a
      class="wp-block-button__link has-base-color has-custom-color-2-background-color has-text-color has-background has-link-color wp-element-button"
      >Primary CTA</a
    >
  </div>
  <!-- /wp:button -->

  <!-- wp:button {"className":"is-style-outline","textColor":"custom-color-1","style":{"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|custom-color-1"}}},"border":{"color":"var:preset|color|custom-color-1"}}} -->
  <div class="wp-block-button is-style-outline">
    <a
      class="wp-block-button__link has-custom-color-1-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-element-button"
      style="border-color:var(--wp--preset--color--custom-color-1)"
      >Secondary CTA</a
    >
  </div>
  <!-- /wp:button -->
</div>
<!-- /wp:buttons -->
```

### Ollie icon block â€” named icon (inline color, no background)

Use a named `ollie-phosphor-*` slug when the icon exists in the Ollie icon library. `iconColorValue` must match the hex of the Ollie color slug used in `iconColor`.

```html
<!-- wp:outermost/icon-block {"iconName":"ollie-phosphor-phone","iconColor":"custom-color-2","iconColorValue":"#0572aa","width":"1.75rem"} -->
<div class="wp-block-outermost-icon-block">
  <div
    class="icon-container has-icon-color has-custom-color-2-color"
    style="color:#0572aa;width:1.75rem;transform:rotate(0deg) scaleX(1) scaleY(1)"
  >
    <svg
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      viewBox="0 0 256 256"
      fill="currentColor"
    >
      <!-- phosphor phone path -->
    </svg>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- /wp:outermost/icon-block -->
```

### Ollie icon block â€” custom SVG with background pill

Use when the icon is a custom/brand SVG not in the Ollie library. Set `iconName` to `""` and embed the full SVG inline. Use `iconBackgroundColor` + `iconBackgroundColorValue` for the pill background. Apply border radius via `var:preset|border-radius|full` to stay on-token. Padding is set in `px` inside `style.spacing.padding` (Ollie Pro does not map padding to spacing tokens for icon blocks).

```html
<!-- wp:outermost/icon-block {"iconName":"","iconBackgroundColor":"custom-color-2","iconBackgroundColorValue":"#0572aa","width":"90px","style":{"border":{"radius":{"topLeft":"var:preset|border-radius|full","topRight":"var:preset|border-radius|full","bottomLeft":"var:preset|border-radius|full","bottomRight":"var:preset|border-radius|full"}},"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"20px","bottom":"20px","left":"5px","right":"5px"}}}} -->
<div class="wp-block-outermost-icon-block">
  <div
    class="icon-container has-icon-background-color has-custom-color-2-background-color"
    style="background-color:#0572aa;width:90px;padding-top:20px;padding-right:5px;padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:5px;border-top-left-radius:var(--wp--preset--border-radius--full);border-top-right-radius:var(--wp--preset--border-radius--full);border-bottom-left-radius:var(--wp--preset--border-radius--full);border-bottom-right-radius:var(--wp--preset--border-radius--full);transform:rotate(0deg) scaleX(1) scaleY(1)"
  >
    <svg
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      viewBox="0 0 {W} {H}"
      role="img"
      aria-labelledby="title desc"
    >
      <title id="title"></title>
      <desc id="desc"></desc>
      <!-- paste full path data here -->
    </svg>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- /wp:outermost/icon-block -->
```

**Key differences between named and custom SVG icons:**

| Attribute     | Named icon (`ollie-phosphor-*`)        | Custom SVG (`iconName: ""`)                             |
| ------------- | -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| `iconName`    | `"ollie-phosphor-{slug}"`              | `""`                                                    |
| Color control | `iconColor` + `iconColorValue`         | `iconBackgroundColor` + `iconBackgroundColorValue`      |
| CSS class     | `has-icon-color has-{slug}-color`      | `has-icon-background-color has-{slug}-background-color` |
| SVG fill      | `fill="currentColor"` (inherits color) | explicit `fill="#fff"` on paths for contrast            |
| Padding       | Not needed (icon fills width)          | Set in `px` via `style.spacing.padding`                 |
| Border radius | Not needed                             | Use `var:preset                                         | border-radius | full` per-corner |
| `viewBox`     | Standard phosphor `0 0 256 256`        | Match the actual SVG artwork dimensions                 |

**Rules:**

- Always set `iconBackgroundColorValue` to the hex that corresponds to the Ollie color slug â€” Ollie Pro writes both.
- Do not invent color slugs. Use only slugs confirmed in context.md.
- The SVG `<title>` and `<desc>` tags are required for accessibility; leave `id="title"` and `id="desc"` even when empty.
- Custom SVG paths must be self-contained â€” no external references, no `<use>`, no `<image>`.
- `transform:rotate(0deg) scaleX(1) scaleY(1)` is always emitted by Ollie Pro; include it verbatim.

### Icon + label contact item

Named icon with a text label that hides on tablet:

```html
<!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"nowrap"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group">
  <!-- wp:outermost/icon-block {"iconName":"ollie-phosphor-phone","iconColor":"custom-color-2","iconColorValue":"#0572aa","width":"1.75rem"} -->
  <div class="wp-block-outermost-icon-block">
    <div
      class="icon-container has-icon-color has-custom-color-2-color"
      style="color:#0572aa;width:1.75rem;transform:rotate(0deg) scaleX(1) scaleY(1)"
    >
      <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        viewBox="0 0 256 256"
        fill="currentColor"
      >
        <path d="M176,208a40.21,40.21,0,0,1-39.9-36.1..."></path>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- /wp:outermost/icon-block -->

  <!-- wp:paragraph {"className":"hide-on-tablet","style":{"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"var:preset|color|base"}}}},"textColor":"base","ollieCustomClasses":["hide-on-tablet"]} -->
  <p class="hide-on-tablet has-base-color has-text-color has-link-color">
    (111) 111-1111
  </p>
  <!-- /wp:paragraph -->
</div>
<!-- /wp:group -->
```

