## Screenshot library

Optional visual reference at `~/pictures/blocks/`.

```bash
# List filenames (do not open images yet)
find ~/pictures/blocks -maxdepth 1 -type f \( -iname '*.png' -o -iname '*.jpg' -o -iname '*.webp' \) -printf '%f\n' | sort

# Find relevant files for a task (adjust terms)
find ~/pictures/blocks -maxdepth 1 -type f \( -iname '*hero*' -o -iname '*card*' -o -iname '*cta*' \) -printf '%f\n' | sort
```

Rules:

- List filenames first; open only 1â€“3 most relevant.
- Cache findings in context.md under `## Block Screenshot References`.
- Do not rescan the folder every run.

